          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A deuterium  gas  was  contained  in a right circular",
                " cylinder of 2.54 cm radius and 3.5  cm  height.  The",
                " walls  were  0.00064 cm havar foil.  The target cell",
                " was designed to be filled to a pressure of 2.0 atm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Five surface-barrier silicon  detectors",
                " mounted   in   the   focal   plane   of  127-degrees",
                " doublefocusing magnet."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The proton angular distribution data were taken at 12",
                " photon energies. In addition an angular distribution",
                " covering 19 angles was measured for Eg = 20.0 (0.25)",
                " MeV.  The equivalent photon cross sections have been",
                " extracted  from the electrodisintegration data using",
                " the virtual photon spectrum technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The equivalent  photon  cross sections were extracted",
                " from  deuteron  electrodisintegration   measurements",
                " over an energy range of 17 to 28 MeV. Proton angular",
                " distributions were measured at  12  photon  energies",
                " and  the  total  cross  section  determined  with an",
                " experimental uncertainty of approximately lower than",
                " 6%.  The differential cross section at angle-cm = 90",
                " degrees was also measured."
              ]
            }
          ],
